{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so she went immediately to talk to him, and she said, oh, I feel so terrible because I saw Paulette a few days ago, and I know that she had all the papers and passport to go to Morocco.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was going to join up there and see Morocco-- I don't think she's here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think she left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he had escaped for the fourth time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He tried three time before.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was picked up again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "For the fourth time, he escaped the prisoner of war camp, and he walked from Germany to France.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the peasants on the way gave him-- one gave him shirt, another one give him a pair of pants.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- I mean, and he didn't have his uniform-- the prisoner uniform anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so he walked and walked until he reached the border of France, and there he took a train and they accept-- all those of course in the trains, they didn't have to have any money to put ticket.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when he came there, and he heard that I had-- that I wasn't there, can imagine how he felt.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that night, I happened to be in a hotel with my children-- I wasn't in a hospital.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And at 4 o'clock in the morning, somebody knocked the door.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, when you survive all that, I mean, you could survive anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Since what?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the time the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From August 1939.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] August or September, '40.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was sure he had been killed.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
